@startuml
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam backgroundColor #fcfcfd
skinparam defaultFontName Helvetica
skinparam defaultFontSize 14
skinparam arrowColor #0f172a
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #fff7d6
skinparam noteBorderColor #b45309
skinparam noteFontColor #334155
skinparam roundcorner 16
title Activity - gdp/GdpPipeline
skinparam activity {
  backgroundColor #f8fafc
  borderColor #0f172a
  fontColor #0f172a
  diamondBackgroundColor #e2e8f0
  diamondBorderColor #1d4ed8
  diamondFontColor #0f172a
  startColor #1d4ed8
  endColor #0f172a
  barColor #1d4ed8
}
start
partition "Observe and Bind" {
:Start from shared flow\nshared/diagrams/shared-reconcile-activity.svg;
:Read desired GdpPipeline spec, tracked status,\nand delete intent;
if ("Tracked or explicit OCI identity present?") then (yes)
:Get the current OCI resource via\nGetGdpPipeline;
else (no)
:Resolve an existing OCI resource through\nListGdpPipelines using filters compartment_id,\ndisplay_name, gdp_pipeline_id, lifecycle_state;
:Create the OCI resource via CreateGdpPipeline\nwhen no reusable match is found;
:Persist the resolved or created OCI identity\ninto status;
endif
}
if ("Delete requested?") then (yes)
partition "Delete" {
:Delete path uses DeleteGdpPipeline with\nrequired via GetGdpPipeline or\nListGdpPipelines to DELETED confirmation;
:Confirm deletion via GetGdpPipeline or\nListGdpPipelines until OCI reaches DELETED;
if ("Delete cleanup and finalizer release succeed?") then (yes)
:Remove the finalizer after delete completion;
else (no)
:Stay blocked until cleanup or finalizer\nrelease succeeds;
endif
}
stop
else (no)
partition "Lifecycle Classification" {
if ("OCI state in retryable set?") then (yes)
:Request requeue while OCI remains in CREATING,\nUPDATING, DELETING;
stop
endif
if ("OCI state is outside success targets?") then (yes)
:Return an unsuccessful reconcile result until\nOCI reaches ACTIVE, INACTIVE;
stop
endif
}
partition "Ready and Drift Handling" {
:Compare live OCI state against the imported\nfield surface;
if ("Force-new or conflicting drift detected?") then (yes)
:Reject drift before OCI mutation for force-new\nfields bucket_details, compartment_id,\npeering_region, pipeline_type;
stop
endif
if ("Supported mutable drift detected?") then (yes)
:Apply UpdateGdpPipeline only for mutable\nfields approval_key_vault_id,\nauthorization_details, defined_tags,\ndescription (+8 more);
else (no)
:Skip the no-op mutation path;
endif
:Run provider helper hooks\ncreate=tfresource.CreateResource,\ntfresource.WaitForWorkRequestWithErrorHandling\nentity=gdppipeline action=CREATED;\nupdate=tfresource.UpdateResource,\ntfresource.WaitForWorkRequestWithErrorHandling\nentity=gdppipeline action=UPDATED;\ndelete=tfresource.DeleteResource,\ntfresource.WaitForWorkRequestWithErrorHandling\nentity=gdppipeline action=DELETED when the\nmatching field-driven path executes;
:Return success for the ACTIVE, INACTIVE\nsuccess state;
:Project required status and finalizer policy\nretain-until-confirmed-delete;
:Requeue on provisioning, updating, terminating;
}
endif
stop
note right
shared diagram:
shared/diagrams/shared-reconcile-activity.svg
Start from the shared reconcile activity and
specialize provider-backed CRUD, wait, and
status-projection details here.
Controller-local activity diagrams add
list-lookup hints, secret policies, delete
handling, and open formal gaps.
archetype batch: Generated service-manager
controllers specialize the shared reconcile path
with formal runtime ownership.
service: gdp
slug: gdppipeline
kind: GdpPipeline
archetype: generated-service-manager
status/finalizer: required /
retain-until-confirmed-delete
requeue: provisioning, updating, terminating
provider states: create CREATING, UPDATING;
update UPDATING; delete DELETING
supported drift: approval_key_vault_id,
authorization_details, defined_tags, description
(+8 more)
reject before mutate: force-new fields
bucket_details, compartment_id, peering_region,
pipeline_type
create-only fields: none
list lookup: oci_gdp_gdp_pipelines filters
compartment_id, display_name, gdp_pipeline_id,
lifecycle_state
conflicts: none
open gaps: none
GdpPipeline create, update, and delete are
work-request-backed. The runtime records the
opening opc-work-request-id, polls
GetGdpWorkRequest through the generatedruntime
async seam, and rereads GetGdpPipeline before
projecting status or completing delete
confirmation.
GDP work-request OperationStatus values
normalize into the shared async classes and GDP
operation types normalize into create, update,
and delete phases. Raw work-request status,
operation type, message, percent complete, and
work-request ID remain visible in
status.async.current for debugging.
Success states are explicit: ACTIVE and INACTIVE
settle success, while NEEDS_ATTENTION is
terminal non-success rather than a default
active state.
Pre-create reuse is exact on compartmentId,
displayName, pipelineType, and peeringRegion,
and the runtime confirms bucketDetails from a
follow-up GET before binding to an existing
pipeline. When a tracked OCID already exists,
list reuse stays keyed to the service-specific
gdpPipelineId filter.
Mutable drift is limited to
UpdateGdpPipelineDetails fields displayName,
description, serviceLogGroupId, fileTypes,
authorizationDetails,
isFileOverrideInDestinationEnabled,
isScanningEnabled, isChunkingEnabled,
isApprovalNeeded, approvalKeyVaultId,
freeformTags, and definedTags. Strings, maps,
and false booleans keep explicit clear intent,
while zero-length fileTypes clears remain
unpublished because the pinned SDK update
request omits empty slices.
Start/Stop/Peer/Rotate/ChangeCompartment
auxiliaries remain out-of-scope drift for the
published contract.
end note
@enduml
